The Rhakk Society<br>
<br>
Appearance:  The Rhakk usualy stand about 7 feet tall, but can reach heights of over 8 feet.  They have pale blue skin, and black, white, or yellow eyes.  Their hands are very<br>
delicate and can perform amny percise actions.  The Rhakk’s muscle fibers are very dense, giving a thin, but powerful, appearance.  The Rhakk have fourteen fingers, seven on each<br>
hand.  Each hand includes two opposable thumbs, giving the Rhakk vary good swimming and artistic technequies.  Rhakk can live upwards of two-hundred andforty years before<br>
death, and some have reached nearly fifty, but this is uncommon.<br>
<br>
Government:  The Rhakk value the elderly most highly in daily society, followed by women. When the Rhakk seek guidance or council, they most often visit one or more of the Yomar, the eldest of those who live amongst the Rhakk.  There are usually about ten Rhakk in the Yomar, followed by an eleventh, the leader, dubbed Yomen.  The Yomen act<br>
as an oligarchy, but rarely ever discuss things as a group, unless there is a major problem.<br>
<br>
Reproduction:  The Rhakk reproduce sexually.  A male and femal meet and meditate near a source of pure water for several hours.  After this time, the male exchanges a strand of<br>
DNA though the touching of palms.  The women will carry the child for six months before giving birth.<br>
<br>
Maturity:  Though it takes around 30 years for a Rhakk to be calm enought to go through the rigorus reproduction ritual, Rhakk grow to understand things such as complicated<br>
speech and motor skill by their first years of life.  Rhakk of the age of 5 are often active in daily routines and converstations, and by this time they are at an average height of four<br>
feet.  For the first five years, Rhakk eat intensively, and grow quickly.  After this period, the metabolic rate slows by over 50%.  Rhakk usually meet full height at the age of 25.<br>
<br>
State of mind:  The Rhakk meditate at least three times a week, four on average.  This give the Rhakk an excited state of being, and many of those who can master and further<br>
grasp ways to meditate can unlock powers unseen.  Many Yomen hav fortold tiny portions of the future, and others have had telekinetic abilitys.  No power as of yet as been great enough to do major physical damage, but it is believed that such power could be obtained.<br>
<br>
Culture:  The Rhakk are a peaceful culture, and work for the better of the group.  There are very few fights, and there has been no known record of murder or suicide.  The Rhakk<br>
are very mentally adept, and love to shape smooth artistic works.  The Rhakk are a very patient people, and will sometimes spend 50 or more years honing a single skill to utter<br>
perfection. The Rhakk love to learn, and are very knowlegable by the time they reach old age.<br>
